Title: Object: Chamber and sarcophagus in the Great Pyramid of Gizah
Series: Views in Egypt, Palestine and other parts of the Ottoman Empire
Description: Plate 6 in volume I: men with turbans inside the chamber, examining the sarcophagus at the end of the room; two men coming in the chamber in the right foreground, one holding a torch; after Mayer. 1801 Hand-coloured aquatint with etching
